Job Description:
* POSITION SUMMARY:
- The Human Resource Manager will lead and direct the routine
functions of the Human Resources (HR) department including hiring
and interviewing staff, administering pay, benefits, and leave, and enforcing company policies and practices.
* ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:
- A human resource manager has two basic functions: overseeing
department functions and managing employees. That's why human
resources managers must be well-versed in each of the human resources
disciplines – compensation and benefits, training and development,
employee relations, and recruitment and selection. Maintains and enhances the
organization's human resources by planning, implementing, and evaluating employee
relations and human resources policies, programs, and practices
The tasks assigned to this position are listed below, categorized as highest, middle and lower priorities:
* Recruitment & Selection
- Manage and ensure the job description is up to date;
• Manage the hiring process, include advertising, reviewing and shortlisting
resumes, coordinating and conducting interviews, conducting reference and
background checks;
• Manage the on-boarding process for new employees;
• Build and keep good relationship with external recruitment agencies and network
* Performance Management:
- Develop the target objective setting procedure and form
- Keep up to date Performance Evaluation form, and make sure that everyone uses
the same form for evaluation;
• Follow up the tracking process of objective setting;
• Oversee the annual employee review process, preparing scoring report;
• Manage performance evaluation, competency framework, staffing, training and development, KPI setting
* Training and Development:
- Oversee the training and development programs include, discussing, analyzing
the training needs for employee;
• Prepare yearly training calendar and budgeting;
• Track on the staff satisfactory on the training program;
• Develop training plan, learning program to support company’s business strategy
* Compensation & Benefit:
Review and update the compensation and benefit for employee as per market
scale;
• Set up bonus and annual salary increment in line with yearly performance review;
• Oversee the payroll calculation;
• Oversee the insurance policies and process include NSSF and private insurance
* Compliance:
Maintain and update the employee handbook and organizational staffing chart;
• Ensure that the company policies comply with Cambodian labor law;
• Develop policies and procedures in line with the company objectives and
operations;
• Dealing with labor inspectors
* Personnel:
Develop cooperate plan for HR matters such as; workforce, compensation, salary
scale, benefit, safety and health;
• Review existing HR policies and procedures and propose for change if needed;
• Oversee the preparation of all formal letter such drafting the offer letter,
employment contract, Recommendation, Internship Certificate, Salary Certificate
* MIDDLE PRIORITY:
• Provide guidance, coaching, counseling, discipline to staff;
• Perform other tasks as assigned by Management Team.
* LOWER PRIORITY:
- Provide guidance, coaching, counseling, discipline to staff

