Job Description:
ULS is seeking a Project Manager to oversee 1-2 individual real estate projects from concept to handover to ensure projects are delivered on time and on budget. This position is both managerial and technical, and candidates should bring years of first-hand real estate project expertise to this role in addition to demonstrating exceptional project management
skills.

* Specifically, this position will focus in the following areas, in order of priority:
Design & Construction Management ~40% of total work
-  Develop project schedules and directly manage internal Project Assistants;
- Create and issue Request for Proposals (RFP’s) for architectural, structural, MEP, and other consulting services;
- Oversee architectural, structural, and MEP design consultants during the design phase to ensure projects are delivered in line with ULS’ vision;
- Directly manage tendering process for construction works in coordination with third-party quantity surveyors;
- Oversee value engineering of project designs prior to construction and award construction contracts to exceptional contractors;
- Serve as the key decision maker between all parties during the design, construction, and tender phases;
- Report weekly and monthly progress to the Project Development Director and all other relevant project stakeholders
- Perform site visits to active construction sites and participate in weekly construction site meetings;
- Provide final quality assurance reviews to ensure project handover meets defined standards and expectations.

Legal & Operations ~20% of total work
- Organize consulting and construction contracts in coordination with third-party legal consultants and the Project Development Director;
- Confirm contract milestones outlined in contract agreements have been successfully achieved;
- Oversee and manage final assets during the operations and
maintenance project phase;
- Initiate new legal entity incorporations for long-term operation management when requested by the Executive team

Financial Oversight ~20% of total work
- Develop financial models in consultation with Managing Director, Project Development Director, and the internal Finance Team;
- Define preliminary costing and determine project budgets;
- Develop pricing strategy in consultation with the Managing Director, Project Development Director, and the internal Finance Team;
- Assist the internal Finance Team with project accounting and financial reporting tasks as necessary;
- Review and approve invoicing and issuance of payments to consultants and vendors in coordination with the internal Finance Team;
- Monitor and report financial performance of projects in addition to overseeing cash flow management

Sales and Leasing Management ~10% of total work
- Coordinate with in-house Sales Team to develop sales strategies;
- Coordinate with Marketing and Communications Department on all relevant project marketing materials;
- Identify strategic retail operating partners and coordinate leasing and operating contracts;
- Ensure authorized sales agencies are selling on brand to correct target markets;
- Evaluate and monitor sales activities and profitability
Project

Development & Concept Design ~10% of total work
- Aid Company Partners on assessing overall project feasibility;
- Research target markets and develop understanding of microeconomic and macro-economic trends;
- Develop architectural and other consultant briefs;
- Oversee application process for construction permits and obtain a firm understanding of zoning restrictions;
- Advise Partners and Marketing & Communications department on project brand development;
- Develop firm knowledge of domestic real estate market behavior;
- Identify internal staffing needs and oversee recruitment process

Job Requirement:
- Bachelor’s Degree in Construction Management, Project Management, Civil Engineering, or Real Estate Development or similar;
- Additional certifications such as PMP or PRINCE and/or LEED accreditations are appreciated;
- 10+ years of professional experience managing construction projects with preference for experience with projects over 10 floors;
- Strong organizational and time management skills, with an attention to detail;
- Advanced skills in Microsoft Project, Microsoft Office, Microsoft Word, and AutoCad;
- Autodesk certifications and/or experience with Building Information Modeling (BIM) is highly sought after;
- Experience with the LEED accreditation system or other green building accreditation systems is appreciated;
- Excellent written and verbal communication skills and well-developed presentation skills;
- Must be able to work in a fast-paced environment, have the ability to multi-task, and be eager to learn new skills;.
- Languages: Fluent in English, competency in either Khmer or Chinese (Mandarin) preferred but not essential

Working hours: Up to 48 hours per week; primary work days are Monday to Friday with work outside of office hours required on occasions.
Location: Phnom Penh, Cambodia.
Reports to: This position reports to the Project Development Director.
Compensation: ULS is offering a competitive base salary commensurate with experience.
Benefits: This position comes with international medical coverage and unlimited holiday leave

